From: VyOS LS1046A Build <build@vyos.io>
Date: Sat, 18 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] usb: host: xhci-plat: force XHCI_AVOID_BEI on LS1046A DWC3

On the NXP LS1046A the Synopsys DesignWare USB3 controller posts Block
Event Interrupts (BEI) on bulk TRBs in a way the xHCI host state
machine mishandles when the TRB ring wraps: a genuine transfer event
that arrives after a BEI-suppressed event is misattributed to a stale
slot/endpoint and the xHCI internal command timer eventually fires,
marking the HC dead.

On our Mono Gateway (fsl,ls1046a-dwc3 controller at 2f00000.usb) the
reproducer is:

  [   11.77] usb 1-1: new high-speed USB device number 2 using xhci-hcd
  [   11.94] usb 1-1: Product: Ultra / Manufacturer: SanDisk
      (usb-storage begins probe; SCSI INQUIRY bulk-IN stalls)
  [   17.24] xhci-hcd: xHCI host not responding to stop endpoint command
  [   17.25] xhci-hcd: xHCI host controller not responding, assume dead
  [   17.26] xhci-hcd: HC died; cleaning up
  [   17.26] probe of 1-1 returned 0 after 5301765 usecs

Reading the xHCI quirks word printed during init confirms the bit is
missing:

  [   11.45] xhci-hcd: hcc params 0x0220f66d hci version 0x100 quirks
             0x0000008002008410

(XHCI_TRUST_TX_LENGTH 0x400 is present but XHCI_AVOID_BEI 0x8000 is
not.)

The existing userspace workaround of passing `xhci_hcd.quirks=0x8400`
on the kernel command line has no effect here because xhci-plat.c does
not consume the xhci_hcd module parameter (that path is PCI-only). Add
the quirk at the platform-quirks hook for any xHCI whose parent tree
contains a fsl,ls1046a-dwc3 node. XHCI_TRUST_TX_LENGTH is already set
by default on xhci-plat; we add both for safety since the DWC3
databook documents the same TX-length residue issue addressed by
TRUST_TX_LENGTH on this SoC.

Reviewed by grepping drivers/usb/host/xhci-plat.c in v6.6 — the hook
point xhci_plat_quirks() is called from xhci_gen_setup() during host
reset, before any TRB is queued. No runtime behaviour changes on other
boards (guarded by of_device_is_compatible()).

Signed-off-by: VyOS LS1046A Build <build@vyos.io>
---
 drivers/usb/host/xhci-plat.c | 14 ++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 14 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/usb/host/xhci-plat.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/host/xhci-plat.c
@@ -76,8 +76,22 @@ static int xhci_priv_resume_quirk(struct usb_hcd *hcd)
 static void xhci_plat_quirks(struct device *dev, struct xhci_hcd *xhci)
 {
 	struct xhci_plat_priv *priv = xhci_to_priv(xhci);
+	struct device *tmpdev;
 
 	xhci->quirks |= priv->quirks;
+
+	/*
+	 * NXP LS1046A DWC3 errata: the controller posts BEI on bulk TRBs
+	 * in a way that confuses the xHCI event handler when the ring
+	 * wraps, leading to "xHCI host controller not responding, assume
+	 * dead" during USB-storage probe. Force XHCI_AVOID_BEI plus the
+	 * related XHCI_TRUST_TX_LENGTH which is documented for the SoC.
+	 */
+	for (tmpdev = dev; tmpdev; tmpdev = tmpdev->parent) {
+		if (tmpdev->of_node &&
+		    of_device_is_compatible(tmpdev->of_node, "fsl,ls1046a-dwc3"))
+			xhci->quirks |= XHCI_AVOID_BEI | XHCI_TRUST_TX_LENGTH;
+	}
 }
 
 /* called during probe() after chip reset completes */
